Scraping the scoot loop data:

Dependencies:

I use 5 packages to scrape the scoot data.

library(httr) # Tools for Working with URLs and HTTP, CRAN v1.4.2     
library(jsonlite) # A Simple and Robust JSON Parser and Generator for R, CRAN v1.7.1 
library(tidyverse) # Easily Install and Load the 'Tidyverse', CRAN v1.3.0
library(lubridate) # Make Dealing with Dates a Little Easier, CRAN v1.7.9
library(cronR) # Schedule R Scripts and Processes with the 'cron' Job Scheduler, CRAN v0.4.2
library(taskscheduleR) # # Schedule R Scripts/Processes with Windows Task Scheduler, CRAN v1.4

Code for accessing the data:

The first step is to extract the raw data from the TfGM API using httr::GET() and the following url: "“https://api.tfgm.com/odata/ScootLoops?$expand=EndLocation,StartLocation,ScootDetails&$top=4000”

I am also using the following subscription key:“972db18168b84d30a2db59901c9162ce”.

raw <- GET("https://api.tfgm.com/odata/ScootLoops?$expand=EndLocation,StartLocation,ScootDetails&$top=4000",
           add_headers("Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key"= "972db18168b84d30a2db59901c9162ce"))
raw

Code for cleaning the data:

Then clean the data using tidyverse functions:

junction_data <- fromJSON(rawToChar(raw$content))$value %>%
  filter(str_detect(SCN, "^N22161"),
         SCN != 'N22161N')%>%
  unnest_wider(ScootDetails, names_repair = "unique") %>%
  mutate(start_coords = StartLocation$LocationSpatial$Geography$WellKnownText,
         start_lat = as.numeric(gsub(".* ([-]*[0-9]+[.][0-9]+).*", "\\1", start_coords)),
         start_long = as.numeric(gsub(".*?([-]*[0-9]+[.][0-9]+).*", "\\1", start_coords)),
         end_coords = EndLocation$LocationSpatial$Geography$WellKnownText,
         end_lat = as.numeric(gsub(".* ([-]*[0-9]+[.][0-9]+).*", "\\1", end_coords)),
         end_long = as.numeric(gsub(".*?([-]*[0-9]+[.][0-9]+).*", "\\1", start_coords)),
         time = lubridate::now(tzone = "GMT"))%>%
  janitor::clean_names()%>%
  select(scoot_name = scn_2,
         description,
         time,
         congestion_percentage,
         current_flow,
         average_speed,
         link_travel_time,
         start_lat,
         start_long,
         end_lat,
         end_long) %>%
  as_tibble()

Code for saving the data:

time <- gsub(" |:","_",Sys.time())

junction_data %>%
  write_csv(
    paste0("/Users/nathankhadaroo/Desktop/PhD/CCAP_project/Data/",time,".csv")
    )

Scheduling the API calls:

I use cronR when using my laptop and TaskscheduleR on my university desktop.

“tfgm_webscrape.R” refers to a script with the above code.

Using cronR:

# Load packages: ----------------------------------------------------------

library(cronR) # Schedule R Scripts and Processes with the 'cron' Job Scheduler, CRAN v0.4.2
library(dplyr) # A Grammar of Data Manipulation, CRAN v1.0.2
library(readr) # Read Rectangular Text Data, CRAN v1.3.1

# Tell cron which script to run: ------------------------------------------

cmd <- cron_rscript("tfgm_webscrape.R")

# Start schedule: ---------------------------------------------------------

cron_add(command = cmd,
         frequency = "minutely",
         id = "job",
         description = 'scrapes_scoot_from_tfgm')

# Stop schedule: ----------------------------------------------------------

cronR::cron_clear()

# Merging files: ----------------------------------------------------------

data <- list.files(path="Data", full.names = TRUE) %>% 
  lapply(read_csv) %>% 
  bind_rows %>%
  arrange(scoot_name)

# Saving the data: --------------------------------------------------------

data %>%
  write_csv("Data/scoot_data.csv")

Scraping the Telraam sensors:

This is some test code which scrapes the telraam API, these sensors are not in place yet so I have tested this on the nearest existing sensor.

Loading libraries:

library(httr) # Tools for Working with URLs and HTTP, CRAN v1.4.2     
library(jsonlite) # A Simple and Robust JSON Parser and Generator for R, CRAN v1.7.1 
library(tidyverse) # Easily Install and Load the 'Tidyverse', CRAN v1.3.0
library(lubridate) # Make Dealing with Dates a Little Easier, CRAN v1.7.9

Making the API call:

Using the httr package to make the call automatically:

raw <- POST("https://telraam-api.net/v0/traffic",
                 body = list("level" = "segments",
                 "format" = "per-hour",
                 "id" = "9000000019",
                 "time_start"= "2020-12-01 00:00:00Z",
                 "time_end"= "2020-12-08 24:00:00Z"),
                 encode = "json")

Checking that the call was successful:

raw
## Response [https://telraam-api.net/v0/traffic]

Status is 200!

Transforming the data into something useable:

df <- fromJSON(rawToChar(raw$content)) %>%
  mutate(date = lubridate::ymd_hms(date))

Plotting traffic counts:

For the last week:

df %>% ggplot(aes(x = date)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = car, colour = "Cars")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = pedestrian, colour = "Pedestrians")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = bike, colour = "Bikes")) +
  geom_line(aes(y = heavy,colour = "Heavy Vehicules")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Traffic counts:", subtitle = "Hourly:", x = "Time:", y = "Count:", colour = "Type:")

And for just yesterday:

df %>%
